    "best_candidate": "candidate_2",
    "improvements_made": "1. Split the generic STATUS entity into three dedicated lookup tables (APPLICATION_STATUS, CARD_STATUS, LETTER_STATUS) to simplify joins and reflect distinct status domains. 2. Changed Review relationship to 1:N, allowing multiple review entries per application for audit trails. 3. Added LETTER_STATUS foreign key (letter_status_code) to explicitly capture confirmation vs. rejection instead of relying solely on free‑text letter_type. 4. Standardized timestamp attribute names across all entities to created_at and updated_at for consistency. 5. Renamed requested_card_type to requested_card_type_id and linked it to CARD_TYPE. 6. Ensured all entities have appropriate primary keys and foreign key references, preserving the comprehensive coverage of the original model while improving clarity and extensibility."
